President Trump on Saturday heralded gains made against the coronavirus pandemic and the relatively low mortality rate in the U.S. compared to other hard-hit countries.
Belgium, the U.K., Italy, France, the Netherlands, Spain, Iran and China had higher per capita mortality rates.
Belgium had the highest per capita mortality rate of 14.3% per 100,000 people.
The U.K., Italy, France, the Netherlands and Spain each had double-digit per capita mortality rates.
The data shows China with a mortality rate of 5.5% per 100,000, according to the JHU study.